      • linkTwoMaps

        private void linkTwoMaps​(MapBase mapA,
                         MapBase mapB,
                         int[] linkCoorOnA,
                         int[] linkCoorOnB)
        Private method used to create a link between two maps (mapA and mapB). The link tile displays the text "Doorway", if the player moves onto this tile, they will exit the current map and emerge on the corresponding link on the map being linked to.
        Parameters:
        mapA - the first map.
        mapB - the second map.
        linkCoorOnA - the coordinates of the link on mapA.
        linkCoorOnB - the coordinates of the corresponding link on mapB.
